Three circles of radius $ 1$ are externally tangent to each other and internally tangent to a larger circle. What is the radius of the large circle?\\
\\

\begin{asy}
import olympiad;
import cse5;
defaultpen(white);
size(100);
unitsize(0.8cm);
defaultpen(linewidth(.8pt)+fontsize(8pt));

real r = 1 + (2/3)*(sqrt(3));
pair A = dir(47.5)*(r - 1);
pair B = dir(167.5)*(r - 1);
pair C = dir(-72.5)*(r - 1);

draw(Circle(A,1));
draw(Circle(B,1));
draw(Circle(C,1));
draw(Circle(origin,r));
\end{asy}
\\
\\
\\
$ \textbf{(A)}\ \frac{2 + \sqrt{6}}{3}\qquad 
\textbf{(B)}\ 2\qquad 
\textbf{(C)}\ \frac{2 + 3\sqrt{2}}{3}\qquad 
\textbf{(D)}\ \frac{3 + 2\sqrt{3}}{3}\qquad 
\textbf{(E)}\ \frac{3 + \sqrt{3}}{2}$
